# Architecture Explanation

The application follows layered architecture.

## Controller Layer

Handles incoming REST API requests.

## Service Layer

Contains business logic for reward calculation.

## Repository Layer

Handles database operations using Spring Data JPA.

## DTO Layer

Transfers response data between layers.


---

# API Endpoint Details

## Get Customer Rewards

### Endpoint

GET /api/rewards


### Sample Response

json
[
  {
    "customerId": 1,
    "customerName": "John",
    "monthlyRewards": {
      "JANUARY": 115,
      "FEBRUARY": 250
    },
    "totalRewards": 365
  },
  {
    "customerId": 2,
    "customerName": "Alice",
    "monthlyRewards": {
      "MARCH": 120
    },
    "totalRewards": 120
  }
]
```

---

# Database Configuration

## Create Database

sql
CREATE DATABASE rewards;


## application.properties

serverport=8080

spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/rewards?useSSL=false&serverTimezone=UTC
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=ItsRoot@123
spring.datasource.driver-class-name=com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true

spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true
spring.jpa.properties
